# Intuition
<!-- Describe your first thoughts on how to solve this problem. -->
Remove the duplicates from the linked list !!

# Approach
<!-- Describe your approach to solving the problem. -->
1. Initialize two pointers, prev and curr, with the first and the second nodes of the linked list, respectively.
2. While curr is not NULL, compare the value of curr and prev nodes.
3. If they have the same value, update prev->next to curr->next and move curr to the next node.
4. If they have different values, move both prev and curr to their next nodes.
5. Return the head of the modified linked list.

