Simple solution with slow & fast pointers, that only starts swapping once the 1st zero is found.
Although using only the second loop starting from 0 with left = 0 will work, the first loop prevents redundant swaps for inputs like [1, 3, 1, 5, 2, 5, 1, 6, 0, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0], 

Time: O(n)
Space: O(1)

```
class Solution(object):
    def moveZeroes(self, nums):

		# Set slow pointer to the 1st zero.
        for left in range(len(nums)):
            if nums[left] == 0:
                break

		# Swap elements at fast & slow if fast points to a non-zero number (and increment).
        for right in range(left + 1, len(nums)):
            if nums[right] != 0:
                nums[left], nums[right] = nums[right], nums[left]
                left += 1

```

