**O(N) time and O(1) space.**

We will use a left pointer to keep track of first leftmost zero's position. Whenever some non-zero element is found we will swap that element with this left pointer position and move the pointer one step ahead in array.

Look for code comments for better understanding.
```
class Solution {
public:
    void moveZeroes(vector<int>& nums) {

        int left = 0;

        // Finding first zero to set our left pointer to point to first zero.
        while(left < nums.size() && nums[left] != 0)
            left++;

        // start iterating now after first found zero.
        for(int i=left+1;i<nums.size();i++)
        {
            // If zero found do nothing and move forward.
            if(nums[i] == 0)
                continue;

            // If non-zero elm then swap the left pointer pointing to zero with this element and move our left pointer forward.
            swap(nums[i],nums[left]);
            left++;
        }

    }
};
```

