**Guys here I am goinng to explain the whole thing considering two following cases:**

# **CASE I: When Relative order of non-zero elements need not to be maintained**

STEP 1: Take Two pointers **Start** and **End** for first index and the last index of the array
STEP 2: If the element at Start is 0  swap  it with the value at  end and increment the **start** and decrement the **end**
STEP 3: If the element is not 0; increase the **start**

The code for above approach is given below;
```
 public void moveZeroes(int[] nums) {

    int start=0;
    int end=nums.length-1;

        while (start<end)
        {
            if (nums[start]==0)
            {
                int temp=nums[start];
                nums[start]=nums[end];
                nums[end]=temp;
                start++;
                end--;
            }
            else
            {
                start++;
            }

        }

    }
```

Here for input **nums=[0,1,0,3,12];**
**output=[12,1,3,0,0];**

All the zeroes have been pushed at the end but the relative order of non-zero elements are not maintained.

NOW lets see How can we maintain the relative order while pushing the zeroes at end

# **CASE II: When Relative order of non-zero elements need to be maintained**
STEP 1: Take two pointers **i** and **j** set them to zero
STEP 2: If element at index **i** is not zero; Swap it with element at **j** and increase **j**
STEP 3: increase index **i** for both situation ......swapping occurs or not **I** will increase

**The code for the above approach is given below:**
```
 public void moveZeroes(int[] nums) {

    int i=0;
    int j=0;
    while (i<nums.length)
    {
        if (nums[i]!=0)
        {
            int temp=nums[i];
            nums[i]=nums[j];
            nums[j]=temp;
            j++;
        }
        i++;
    }

    }
```



Let me explain with an example input **nums=[0,1,0,3,12]**

start with **i=0** and **j=0**; **n=nums.length=5**

**nums[i]=0** and **nums[j]=0**

  **nums[i]** and **nums[j]** both are 0 , so the condition is false for if statement so our **i** will increase and **j** remains at 0.

```
  Now i=1 and j=0  ; nums[i]=1  and nums[j]=0
  so nums[i]!=0 so now **SWAPPING** occurs and array becomes nums=[1,0,0,3,12] ; 
  j is incremented to 1 and i is incremented to 2.
```

  Now **i=2** and **j=1**  ; **nums[i]=0**  and **nums[j]=0**
   so **nums[i]!=0** condition is false; no swapping occurs and **i** is increased to 3


     Now i=3 and j=1  ; nums[i]=3  and nums[j]=0
	  so nums[i]!=0 so now **SWAPPING** occurs and array becomes nums=[1,3,0,0,12] ;          
